==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kindergarten
<hw>Kin"der*gar`ten</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., lit.,
children's garden; <ets>kinder</ets> (pl. of <ets>kind</ets> child, akin
to E. <ets>kin</ets> kindred) + <ets>garten</ets> garden.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A class within a primary school or a separate school
for young children, usually between the ages of four and six years,
designed to adapt children to the classroom environment before beginning
academic training, on the theory that education should be begun by
gratifying and cultivating the normal aptitude for exercise, play,
observation, imitation, and construction; -- a name given by
<person>Friedrich Froebel</person>, a German educator, who introduced
this method of training, in rooms opening on a garden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kindergartner</ent>⟦br⟧
